          "order": 2,
          "title": "[https://archive.ph/MxjGW?utm_source=tldrnewsletter]",
          "summary": "UC San Diego Health, UW Health, and Stanford Health Care are testing a tool that uses OpenAI's GPT to read patient messages and draft responses from their doctors. The pilot program aims to see if AI can cut the time medical staff spend responding to patients' online queries. Early responses required heavy editing. The team is working to improve replies and to add a kind bedside manner. Preliminary data suggests that AI could add value as it scored better than real doctors at responding to patient queries posted online.",
